<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,519,1893,1920]" pageId="10" pageNumber="169">
Type material. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gajbe" authorityYear="2004" box="[333,512,1893,1920]" class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Evippa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="10" pageNumber="169" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mandlaensis">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[333,512,1893,1920]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="169">E. mandlaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
Female 
<typeStatus box="[616,714,1893,1919]" pageId="10" pageNumber="169">holotype</typeStatus>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[784,868,1894,1920]" name="India" pageId="10" pageNumber="169">INDIA</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion box="[879,1072,1893,1919]" country="India" name="Madhya Pradesh" pageId="10" pageNumber="169">Madhya Pradesh</collectingRegion>
: Mandla (= Mandala): Narayanganj (
<geoCoordinate box="[216,396,1929,1955]" degrees="22" direction="north" minutes="49" orientation="latitude" pageId="10" pageNumber="169" precision="1" seconds="38.41" value="22.827337">22°49’38.41’’N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate box="[409,586,1929,1955]" degrees="80" direction="east" minutes="14" orientation="longitude" pageId="10" pageNumber="169" precision="1" seconds="10.73" value="80.23631">80°14’10.73’’E</geoCoordinate>
), 
<quantity box="[607,680,1929,1956]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.31" pageId="10" pageNumber="169" unit="m" value="431.0">431 m</quantity>
alt.; U.A. Gajbe leg.; 
<date box="[935,1127,1929,1956]" pageId="10" pageNumber="169" value="1985-01-23">23 January 1985</date>
; repository NZC-ZSI, Kolkata (no register number specified), examined. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[688,803,1965,1992]" pageId="10" pageNumber="169">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kronestedt &amp; Zyuzin" authorityYear="2009" box="[688,796,1965,1992]" class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Wadicosa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="10" pageNumber="169" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fidelis">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[688,796,1965,1992]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="169">W. fidelis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
<typeStatus box="[812,924,1966,1992]" pageId="10" pageNumber="169">Lectotype</typeStatus>
male from ‘Palestine’ (
<collectionCode box="[1192,1282,1965,1991]" pageId="10" pageNumber="169">OXUM</collectionCode>
, collection of O. Pickard-Cambridge: bottle 1572, tube 39), not examined. 
<bibRefCitation author="Kronestedt, T. &amp; Zyuzin, A. A." box="[840,1163,2001,2027]" pageId="10" pageNumber="169" pagination="813 - 828" refId="ref6175" refString="Kronestedt, T. &amp; Zyuzin, A. A. (2009) Fixation of Lycosa fidelis O. Pickard-Cambridge, 1872 as the type species for the genus Wadicosa Zyuzin, 1985 (Araneae: Lycosidae), with a redescripton of the species. Contributions to Natural History, 12, 813 - 828. [incl. corrigendum: Vol. 13 / 2010: 89]" type="journal article" year="2009">Kronestedt &amp; Zyuzin (2009)</bibRefCitation>
illustrated the male and female genitalia of this species and their female genitalic illustrations (
<bibRefCitation author="Kronestedt, T. &amp; Zyuzin, A. A." box="[934,1239,151,177]" pageId="11" pageNumber="170" pagination="813 - 828" refId="ref6175" refString="Kronestedt, T. &amp; Zyuzin, A. A. (2009) Fixation of Lycosa fidelis O. Pickard-Cambridge, 1872 as the type species for the genus Wadicosa Zyuzin, 1985 (Araneae: Lycosidae), with a redescripton of the species. Contributions to Natural History, 12, 813 - 828. [incl. corrigendum: Vol. 13 / 2010: 89]" type="journal article" year="2009">Kronestedt &amp; Zyuzin 2009</bibRefCitation>
: figs 15, 17) were used for comparative purpose.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,150,501]" pageId="11" pageNumber="170">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,556,222,249]" pageId="11" pageNumber="170">Justification of the synonymy.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Gajbe, U. A." box="[564,712,223,249]" pageId="11" pageNumber="170" pagination="1 - 40" refId="ref6099" refString="Gajbe, U. A. (2004) Studies on some spiders of the family Lycosidae (Araneae: Arachnida) from Madhya Pradesh, India. Records of the Zoological Survey of India, Occasional Paper, 221, 1 - 40." type="journal article" year="2004">Gajbe (2004)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gajbe" authorityYear="2004" box="[834,1005,223,249]" class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Evippa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="11" pageNumber="170" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mandlaensis">
<emphasis box="[834,851,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="170">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[865,1005,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="170">mandlaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on a female specimen collected in 
<collectingRegion box="[182,374,259,285]" country="India" name="Madhya Pradesh" pageId="11" pageNumber="170">Madhya Pradesh</collectingRegion>
. Detailed examination of the 
<typeStatus box="[712,810,259,285]" pageId="11" pageNumber="170">holotype</typeStatus>
showed no differences between this species and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kronestedt &amp; Zyuzin" authorityYear="2009" class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Wadicosa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="11" pageNumber="170" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fidelis">
<emphasis box="[1372,1395,259,284]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="170">W</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="170">fidelis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a widely distributed species, which was previously recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[963,1021,295,321]" name="India" pageId="11" pageNumber="170">India</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Tikader, B. K. &amp; Malhotra, M. S." box="[1036,1329,295,321]" pageId="11" pageNumber="170" pagination="248 - 447" refId="ref6874" refString="Tikader, B. K. &amp; Malhotra, M. S. (1980) Lycosidae (Wolf-spiders). Fauna India, Araneae, 1, 248 - 447." type="journal article" year="1980">Tikader &amp; Malhotra 1980</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Lu, T. &amp; Wang, L. Y. &amp; Hadole, P. &amp; Zhang, Z. S." pageId="11" pageNumber="170" pagination="130 - 142" refId="ref6246" refString="Lu, T., Wang, L. Y., Hadole, P. &amp; Zhang, Z. S. (2016) Redescription of four wolf-spiders (Araneae: Lycosidae) from India. Indian Journal of Arachnology, 5, 130 - 142." type="journal article" year="2016">
Lu 
<emphasis box="[1380,1437,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="170">et al.</emphasis>
2016
</bibRefCitation>
) (compare 
<figureCitation box="[338,470,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1673,1697]" captionTargetBox="[155,1429,186,1642]" captionTargetId="figure-21@12.[151,1436,181,1649]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 10. Wadicosa fidelis (O. Pickard-Cambridge, 1872), holotype of Evippa mandlaensis Gajbe, 2004. A female habitus (Ar-1621), dorsal. B–C genitalia: B epigynum, ventral; C vulva, dorsal. D label from type tube. Scale bars: A, 2 mm; B–C, 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4805805" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4805805/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="170">Fig. 10B–C</figureCitation>
with 
<bibRefCitation author="Kronestedt, T. &amp; Zyuzin, A. A." box="[535,843,331,357]" pageId="11" pageNumber="170" pagination="813 - 828" refId="ref6175" refString="Kronestedt, T. &amp; Zyuzin, A. A. (2009) Fixation of Lycosa fidelis O. Pickard-Cambridge, 1872 as the type species for the genus Wadicosa Zyuzin, 1985 (Araneae: Lycosidae), with a redescripton of the species. Contributions to Natural History, 12, 813 - 828. [incl. corrigendum: Vol. 13 / 2010: 89]" type="journal article" year="2009">Kronestedt &amp; Zyuzin 2009</bibRefCitation>
: figs 15, 17). Thus, we consider 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gajbe" authorityYear="2004" box="[1213,1385,331,357]" class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Evippa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="11" pageNumber="170" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mandlaensis">
<emphasis box="[1213,1230,331,356]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="170">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1245,1385,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="170">mandlaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kronestedt &amp; Zyuzin" authorityYear="2009" box="[365,470,367,393]" class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Wadicosa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="11" pageNumber="170" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fidelis">
<emphasis box="[365,388,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="170">W</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[402,470,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="170">fidelis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="170" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,150,501]" pageId="11" pageNumber="170">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,403,429]" pageId="11" pageNumber="170">Remarks.</emphasis>
The NZC-ZSI collection has one glass tube for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gajbe" authorityYear="2004" box="[852,1023,403,429]" class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Evippa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="11" pageNumber="170" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mandlaensis">
<emphasis box="[852,1023,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="170">E. mandlaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, labeled as ‘holotype’ (Ar-1621) and containing 
<specimenCount box="[278,403,439,465]" pageId="11" pageNumber="170" type="female">one female</specimenCount>
specimen in fairly good condition, with broken legs. The same tube has a small glass vial containing the dissected genitalia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
